NAME

	shell

SYNOPSIS

	#include <stdio.h>
	#include <stdlib.h>
	#include <string.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	#include <sys/types.h>
	#include <sys/wait.h>
	#include <signal.h>

DESCRIPTION

	the shell function displays a prompt waiting for the user to type a command before executing it.
	The prompt is re-displayed each time a command has been executed. the "end of file" condition is handled by Ctrl+D, which terminates the function
	it can be used in interactive or non-interactive mode

EXAMPLES OF USAGE:

	$ ./shell
	/bin/ls
	/bin/pwd
	$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./shell
	$ echo "/bin/pwd" | ./shell

RETURN VALUE

	the shell function will always return 0 but the output values are different for errors

	EXAMPLE OF OUTPUT ERRORS:		

ERRORS

	If an executable cannot be found, print an error message and display the prompt again.

